        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9116011">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                for all item numbers in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen freon compressor upper mounting bracket thru bolt (Item 8 ,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen (back-off) the adjusting nuts on the adjusting rod (eye-bolt) (Item 5) to loosen
                    the freon compressor belt.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts that secure the lower freon compressor adjusting bracket (Item 4)
                    to the side of the engine front cover (Item 7).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the adjusting bracket plate (Item 4) along with the adjusting bracket (Item 6)
                    from the adjusting rod (eye-bolt) (Item 5) and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the freon compressor bracket (Item 3) from the forward holes on the bottom of the
                    freon compressor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9116011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9116011.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Discontinued Style Freon Compressor Adjusting Bracket Plate Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FREON COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FREON COMPRESSOR BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ADJUSTING BRACKET PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ADJUSTING ROD (EYE BOLT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. LOWER ADJUSTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ENGINE FRONT COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. UPPER MOUNTING BRACKET THRU BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9116012">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                for all item numbers in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the freon compressor bracket (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116012">Figure 2</hotlnk>) removed in step 5 above, in the rear holes on the
                    bottom of the freon compressor. Tighten to 19 to 23 ft-lbs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new adjusting bracket (Item 6) on the new adjusting bracket plate (Item 4)
                    finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the adjusting bracket (Item 6) onto the adjusting rod (eye-bolt) (Item 5). Install
                    the new adjusting bracket plate (Item 4) and bolts in the two lower mounting holes on the rear of
                    the engine front cover (Item 7) as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9116012">Figure 2</hotlnk>. Tighten to 35 to 40 ft. lbs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust the lower hex nut on the adjusting rod (Item 5) until belt tension of 130 lbs. is
                    obtained if a new belt is used - 100 lbs. if the old belt is used. Tighten the upper hex nut against
                    the lower hex nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the freon compressor upper mounting bracket thru bolt (Item 8) and the adjusting
                    rod (Item 5) and adjusting bracket (Item 6) bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9116012" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9116012.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Redesigned Freon Compressor Adjusting Bracket Plate Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FREON COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FREON COMPRESSOR BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ADJUSTING BRACKET PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ADJUSTING ROD (EYE BOLT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. ADJUSTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ENGINE FRONT COVER UPPER MOUNTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BRACKET THRU BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
